ValueMeaning.preferredDefinition: The mean pressure of the blood within the arterial circulation. The arterial pressure may be directly measured by insertion of an intraarterial catheter connected to a transducer. The mean arterial pressure (MAP) can be calculated by subsequent analysis of the waveform. MAP can be approximated without an invasive procedure using the following formula: diastolic pressure plus 1/3 of the pulse pressure, where pulse pressure is systolic pressure − diastolic pressure.

Concepts.definition: The mean pressure of the blood within the arterial circulation.
